Duke Energy's request to re-classify the new coal-fired unit,
"Unit-6", as a minor source of hazardous air pollutants.

I am concerned that Duke's request to simply redefine the new
coal-fired unit at Cliffside in no way protects public health
and Great Smoky Mountains National Park from the facility's
hazardous pollution. This permitting decision is critical to
North Carolina and the region's air quality and merits full and
fair opportunity for the public to be heard on this issue.
Our energy choices impact our lungs and our state?s most
important natural area, Great Smoky Mountains National Park.
